===Proper noun===
'''Bath'''

#A city in [[England]] (United Kingdom). Romans built a bath there, near some hot springs.

===Noun===
'''bath''' (''plural'' '''baths''')

#A tub or pool which is used for bathing: [[bathtub]].
#A room or area where [[bathe|bathing]] occurs: [[bathroom]].
#The act of bathing.

